HEADWORD: Jamdani
<hw>Jam"da*ni</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A silk fabric,
with a woven pattern of sprigs of flowers.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>jamdanee</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Balfour (Cyc. of
